OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FDry, bright start for most with
OL,6,Fsunny spells, the best of these across
OL,7,FFife and Angus. Cloud soon increasing
OL,8,Ffrom the west with outbreaks of rain
OL,9,Ffor Perthshire and Stirlingshire, the
OL,10,Frain becoming lighter and patchier
OL,11,Flater. Fresh southwesterly winds.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FMostly cloudy at first with
OL,14,Fpatchy rain, otherwise a dry evening
OL,15,Fwith some late sunny spells. Largely
OL,16,Fclear through early hours but becoming
OL,17,Fcloudy with some rain later.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
